attributes.Long form description: The student has to disassemble the KNARREVIK table. The student starts by unscrewing one of the hex socket heads, but the instructor explains that he needs to slightly unscrew all the hex socket heads first and the student follows this instruction using the Allen wrench. Next, the student tries to unscrew one hex socket head and the instructor recommends placing the table on the side to remove the top shelf, the student places the table on the side and proceeds to unscrew all the hex socket heads attached to the tabletop with his hand. Next, the student removes the tabletop. Lastly the student unscrews all the hex socket heads from the shelf with his hands.

attributes.Transcription: Great, now please disassemble this table.

attributes.Action sentence: The student unscrews the hex socket heads of the first leg.

attributes.Transcription: You should start by slighly unscrewing all the screws before.

attributes.Action sentence: The student unscrews the hex socket heads of the second leg.
The student unscrews the hex socket head of the third leg.
The student unscrews the hex socket head of the fourth leg.
The student disassembles the table top.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: Student should lay down the table first.

attributes.Transcription: Now please lay the tab-, the shelf on the side to remove the top shelf.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the first leg.
The student disassembles the second leg.
The student disassembles the third leg.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: Student should first rotate the shelf.

attributes.Transcription: You should rotate the shelf to remove the leg.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the fourth leg.
